# ADR-102 Continuity

- Read in order before implementing: `AGENTS.md`, `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md`, `docs/CHANGELOG.md`, `docs/ADR/102-pre-prod-architectural-cleanup-and-truth-hardening.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/API-BOUNDARY.md`, `docs/DATA-MODEL.md`, `docs/TEST-PLAN.md`, then any ADRs referenced by the chosen slice.
- Treat `docs/ADR/102-pre-prod-architectural-cleanup-and-truth-hardening.md` as the source of truth for the active pre-PROD cleanup backlog and slice execution order.
- `docs/ADR/078-consolidated-follow-through-program.md` is **closed archive**. Do not reopen it or re-derive scope from it; ADR-102 supersedes it as the active program.
- Treat `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md` as the source of truth for the latest completed checkpoint and next slice.
- Treat `docs/CHANGELOG.md` as the source of truth for what has actually landed.
- If ADR, handoff, changelog, and code disagree, stop and reconcile docs before code changes.
- One session = one bounded ADR-102 slice (or tightly coupled sub-item). Do not expand scope or skip the documented order. Minimum PROD path: `0 → 1 → 2 → 9 → 10`.
- At session start, identify the highest-priority unfinished ADR-102 slice whose dependencies are satisfied and restate: current slice, purpose, likely affected files/modules, and what is out of scope.
- Start only from a clean git tree; if dirty, stop and report. Record baseline SHA in the handoff.
- Keep the architecture fully PersAI-native. Do not reintroduce OpenClaw runtime/deploy wiring, compatibility shims, filesystem-owned session state, or TODO scaffolding.
- Touch native OpenClaw only if historical analysis explicitly requires it and a PersAI-side change is insufficient.
- Before ending the session, update `docs/SESSION-HANDOFF.md`, update `docs/CHANGELOG.md` if repo truth changed, update ADR-102 (mark slices complete / adjust backlog) if architecture or active backlog changed, and state the next recommended slice.
